      "writtenOn": "2018-06-01T23:59:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I liked the idea of having a special filelock_create_timeout() function that would allow the caller to specify the timeout, and would fail only if the lock can\u0027t be acquired for that long.\n\nBy the way, the bad side of having these timeouts is that the whole locking thread becomes blocked, which means at the startup the emulator process is unresponsive. But that\u0027s fine if the issue is actually just about retrying",
